Package edu.ncsu.csc316.dsa.set

Interface Set<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - the type of elements stored in the set
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<E>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractSet, HashSet, TreeSet
    public interface Set<E>
extends java.lang.Iterable<E>
    The Set abstract data type represents an unordered collection of elements. Duplicate elements are not allowed in Sets. All Sets must be Iterable to allow clients to iterate using for-each loops. The Set interface is based on the implementation developed for use with the textbook: Data Structures and Algorithms in Java, Sixth Edition Michael T. Goodrich, Roberto Tamassia, and Michael H. Goldwasser John Wiley and Sons, 2014
    Author:
    Dr. King
